topic.title: Lane Reversal

body.p: Lane reversal is supported for both the transmitter and receiver of a given port for a multi-lane link. Lane reversal is supported on any bifurcation up to and including x16. Lane reversal is automatic and requires no user intervention or programming. An example of lane reversal consists of lane 0 of an upstream port attached to lane N-1 of a downstream port where either the downstream or upstream device may reverse the lane order to configure a xN link.

In the tables below, the colored boxes represent the possible placements of a single link partner for bifurcation settings of x16, x8, and x4. Placement of a link partner in one of the colored boxes can be supported with either normal lane ordering or lane reversed ordering.
